The paper deals with denoising of images obtained from optical coherence tomography (OCT), which is a medical imaging technique. The paper proposes a mathematical optimization model to denoise the OCT images, which involves low-rank and sparse priors. This suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization algorithms, which could place it in the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. The use of OCT images also suggests that the paper could belong to the medical imaging (cs.MM) or signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories.
